   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2574_1.jpg"/>

            <opener>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>TELEPHONE</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>PORTISHEAD 29.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <addrLine>FAIRLAWN,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>PORTISHEAD,</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>SOMERSET.</addrLine>
               </address>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1915-09-03">Sept.3.1915</date>
               </dateline>
               <!-- handwritten -->

               <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I am writing to ask whether you have any particulars of the manner in which <persName
                  ref="#ps:FrankGeorge">Frank George</persName> met his death. He was the dearest
               friend I had in the world, and I would give <del rend="crossthrough">a</del>
               everything I have to think that there was a shadow of a doubt about his having been
               killed. I have heard nothing except the bare fact of his death, in a telegram sent me
               by <persName ref="#ps:BerthaGeorge">Miss George</persName>, whom I do not want to
               bother just now.</p>
            <p>Frank used to spend most of his weekends <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2574_2.jpg"/>
               <pb n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2574_3.jpg"/> here with us, and both my wife &amp; myself
               were very fond of him indeed.</p>

            <p>We had a postcard from him, dated August 13, in which he said that their casualties
               had been heartrending, and that they were just going into action again. We hope that
               there is a chance that we may still get another letter from him, written between Aug
                  13<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> and Aug.22<hi rend="superscript">nd.</hi></p>

            <p>Please excuse my troubling you.</p>


            <closer>
               <salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
               <signed>James P. Grieves</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.2574_4.jpg"/>

         </div>
      </body>
